---
import WikiLayout from '../../layouts/WikiLayout.astro';
import DevlogNav from '../../components/DevlogNav.astro';
---
<WikiLayout
  title="Below Deck — April 2026"
  section="devlog"
  description="Demo launch next week! Plus: a behind-the-scenes look at upcoming merchant ships, and our new official wiki."
  ogImage="/images/devlog/april-2026/thumbnail.png"
>
  <div class="wiki-content devlog-entry">

    <div class="entry-meta">
      <a href="/devlog" class="back-link">← All Devlogs</a>
      <span class="entry-date">April 2026</span>
    </div>

    <h1>Demo launch next week 🥳🏴‍☠️</h1>

    <p>Ahoy crew, welcome below deck!</p>
    <p>The next few months are going to be <em>leviathan</em>-huge… We've got the demo launch, Steam Deck Builders Fest, ANZ Indie Showcase, Ocean Fest, Strategems Fest, and Frosty Games Fest.</p>

    <h2>Demo launch: this is it crew!</h2>
    <p>Our demo drops next week, right alongside Steam Deck Builders Fest. This is our biggest milestone to date and <strong>we need YOUR help</strong> to get the game out to as many new players as possible. The best thing you can do is simply… play the demo for at least an hour and then leave a review!</p>

    <div class="info-block">
      <p class="info-label">Launch times:</p>
      <p><strong>USA (PDT)</strong> — 10am, 4th May</p>
      <p><strong>UK</strong> — 6pm, 4th May</p>
      <p><strong>New Zealand (NZT)</strong> — 5am, 5th May</p>
      <p><strong>Australia (AEST)</strong> — 3am, 5th May</p>
    </div>

    <img src="/images/devlog/april-2026/demo-launch.png" alt="Demo Launch — 4th May" class="devlog-img" />

    <h2>What else is on the horizon?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Steam Deck Builder Fest</strong> — May 4–11</li>
      <li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@theindiebrew" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>ANZ Indie Fest &amp; Showcase</strong></a> — May 8–15</li>
      <li><strong>Steam Ocean Fest</strong> — May 19–26</li>
      <li><strong>Steam Strategems Fest</strong> — May 29–June 5</li>
      <li><strong>Steam Frosty Games Fest</strong> — June</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Behind the scenes: Merchant ships</h2>
    <p>Post demo we're going to be moving on to some of our other planned (and highly anticipated) features, including mid-voyage merchant ships! Simon has been exploring the look of these ships, which will have a chaotic, gypsy caravan vibe — stuffed to the brim with curiosities!</p>

    <img src="/images/devlog/april-2026/merchant-ships.png" alt="Merchant ship concept sketches" class="devlog-img" />

    <h2>Our new official Wiki site!</h2>
    <p>Want to learn the ropes? Browse every artefact in the game? Plan peak builds? Now you can! We think our new official wiki is awesome, but don't take our word for it — you're already on it.</p>
    <p>If you haven't explored yet, <a href="/">start here</a>.</p>

    <img src="/images/devlog/april-2026/wiki.png" alt="Davy Jones' Deckhand Wiki" class="devlog-img" />

    <p>Until next time me hearties, yo ho!<br /><br />Ben and the Cass Bay Games Team</p>

    <DevlogNav currentSlug="april-2026" />

  </div>
</WikiLayout>

<style>
  .devlog-entry {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .entry-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    color: var(--ocean);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: var(--gold-dark);
  }

  .entry-date {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .devlog-img {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin: 1.25rem 0;
  }

  .info-block {
    background: var(--navy);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.25rem 0;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
  }

  .info-block p {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    color: rgba(185, 216, 227, 0.9);
  }

  .info-label {
    color: var(--off-white) !important;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem !important;
  }

  .info-block a {
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  li a {
    color: var(--gold);
  }
</style>
